                "name": "Sake Affinity",
                "ability_type": "Supernatural",
                "ability_type_abbrev": "Su",
                "text": "As a swift action, a tanuki can take a swig of sake from the gourd it always carries at its side. When it does so, it gains the effect of one of the following spells at caster level 7th: <i>divine favor</i>, <i>false life</i>, <i>haste</i>, or <i>rage</i>. Unusual tanukis might have additional spell effect choices at the GM\u2019s discretion. Each time a tanuki takes a swig of sake, it becomes progressively drunker and takes a \u20131 penalty to its AC and on Reflex saves for 1 minute. These penalties stack."
            }
